<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h2 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">Extracting only the first read from paired end BAM files</h2><a id="user-content-extracting-only-the-first-read-from-paired-end-bam-files" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: Extracting only the first read from paired end BAM files" href="#extracting-only-the-first-read-from-paired-end-bam-files"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<p dir="auto">Sometimes you only want the first pair of a mate. 0x0040 is hexadecimal
for 64 (i.e. 16 * 4), which is binary for 1000000, corresponding to the
read in the first read pair.</p>
<div class="highlight highlight-source-shell notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" dir="auto" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content="samtools view -b -f 0x0040 eg/ERR188273_chrX.bam &gt; eg/first.bam"><pre>samtools view -b -f 0x0040 eg/ERR188273_chrX.bam <span class="pl-k">&gt;</span> eg/first.bam</pre></div>
<p dir="auto">Once again, you can use <code>flags</code> to verify this (it also accepts
hexadecimal input).</p>
<div class="highlight highlight-source-shell notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" dir="auto" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content="samtools flags 0x0040"><pre>samtools flags 0x0040</pre></div>
