</code></pre></div>
<p dir="auto">The example BAM file only contains reads for <code>chrX</code> hence the statistics
are only returned for <code>chrX</code>.</p>
<p dir="auto">Returning to our coverage definition at the start of this section:</p>
<ol dir="auto">
<li>average depth of each covered base = <code>meandepth</code></li>
<li>percentage of bases covered = <code>covbases</code></li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto">The <a href="https://github.com/brentp/mosdepth">mosdepth</a> tool can also
calculate depth (and much faster than <code>samtools depth</code>) per base or
within a given window. The output is given in a BED file, where the
fourth column indicates the coverage.</p>
